ENTRY       EC 3.6.1.53                 Enzyme
NAME        Mn2+-dependent ADP-ribose/CDP-alcohol diphosphatase;
            Mn2+-dependent ADP-ribose/CDP-alcohol pyrophosphatase;
            ADPRibase-Mn
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on acid anhydrides;
            In phosphorus-containing anhydrides
SYSNAME     CDP-choline phosphohydrolase
REACTION    (1) CDP-choline + H2O = CMP + phosphocholine [RN:R09538];
            (2) ADP-D-ribose + H2O = AMP + D-ribose 5-phosphate [RN:R01054]
ALL_REAC    R01054 R09538
SUBSTRATE   CDP-choline [CPD:C00307];
            H2O [CPD:C00001];
            ADP-D-ribose [CPD:C00301]
PRODUCT     CMP [CPD:C00055];
            phosphocholine [CPD:C00588];
            AMP [CPD:C00020];
            D-ribose 5-phosphate [CPD:C00117]
COMMENT     Requires Mn2+. Unlike EC 3.6.1.13, ADP-ribose diphosphatase, it cannot utilize Mg2+. ADP-D-ribose, CDP-choline, CDP-ethanolamine and ADP are substrates for this enzyme but ADP-D-glucose, UDP-D-glucose, CDP-D-glucose, CDP, CMP and AMP are not hydrolysed [2]. In rat, the enzyme is found predominantly in thymus and spleen.
